# Google OAuth clients for Drive sync (docs/13). Copy to .env and fill in.
#
# Desktop (macOS/Windows/Linux): create a "Desktop" OAuth client in Google Cloud
# Console with the Drive API enabled and the consent screen published "In
# production" (Testing mode expires refresh tokens after 7 days). Until these are
# set, Settings > Sync shows "Google client not configured" and disables sign-in.
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=

# iOS: create a separate "iOS" type OAuth client (Application type: iOS, bundle
# id: com.xinyuan.readingpartner). It has NO client secret. Its id looks like
# 1234567890-abc.apps.googleusercontent.com. Two places must agree:
#   1) Set VITE_GOOGLE_IOS_CLIENT_ID below (the frontend reads it at build time).
#   2) Put the reversed client id into src-tauri/tauri.conf.json under
#      plugins.deep-link.mobile[0].scheme, already set for this repo's client.
#      Reversed form: com.googleusercontent.apps.1234567890-abc (drop the
#      ".apps.googleusercontent.com" suffix, prepend com.googleusercontent.apps.).
#      This registers the Info.plist URL scheme at iOS build time; it cannot come
#      from this env var. See docs/18-iOS-Google登录.md.
VITE_GOOGLE_IOS_CLIENT_ID=

# Android: create a separate "Android" type OAuth client (Application type:
# Android, package name com.xinyuan.readingpartner). Like iOS it has NO client
# secret, but Google additionally requires the SIGNING CERTIFICATE'S SHA-1
# fingerprint — the one from the release keystore the APK is signed with (get it
# with `keytool -list -v -keystore <file> -alias <alias>`, or from the CI
# keystore documented in docs/20-安卓安装.md). Its id looks like
# 1234567890-abc.apps.googleusercontent.com. Two places must agree, same as iOS:
#   1) Set VITE_GOOGLE_ANDROID_CLIENT_ID below.
#   2) Add the reversed client id to src-tauri/tauri.conf.json under
#      plugins.deep-link.mobile[].scheme (that array generates the Android
#      intent-filter at build time; it cannot come from this env var).
# Until this is set, Settings > Sync shows "Google client not configured" on
# Android and sign-in stays disabled (it does not crash).
VITE_GOOGLE_ANDROID_CLIENT_ID=
